   "source": [
    "Q3. How can you customize the appearance of a Bokeh plot, including the axes, title, and legend?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d27eec8b-1b8b-4bee-82ad-3d59a174b01a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In Bokeh, you can customize the appearance of a plot by modifying various attributes of the figure object. Here are some ways to customize the appearance of a Bokeh plot, including the axes, title, and legend:\n",
    "\n",
    "Customizing Axes:\n",
    "\n",
    "To set the labels and title of the x-axis and y-axis, you can use the x_axis_label, y_axis_label, and title attributes of the figure object.\n",
    "To customize the range of values displayed on the axes, you can use the x_range and y_range attributes.\n",
    "To modify the appearance of the tick marks and grid lines, you can use the x_axis_minor_tick_line_color, y_axis_major_tick_line_color, x_axis_grid_line_color, and y_axis_grid_line_color attributes, among others.\n",
    "You can also control the appearance of the tick labels by modifying attributes like x_axis_major_label_text_font_size and y_axis_major_label_text_color.\n",
    "Customizing Title and Legend:\n",
    "\n",
    "To set the title of the plot, you can use the title attribute of the figure object.\n",
    "To add a legend to the plot, you can use the legend attribute. You can customize the position, orientation, and other properties of the legend.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "from bokeh.plotting import figure, show\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prepare the data\n",
    "x = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "y = [6, 7, 2, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the Bokeh figure\n",
    "p = figure(title='My Bokeh Plot', x_axis_label='X-axis', y_axis_label='Y-axis')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Customize axes appearance\n",
    "p.xaxis.axis_label_text_font_size = '14pt'\n",
    "p.yaxis.axis_label_text_font_style = 'italic'\n",
    "p.yaxis.major_label_text_color = 'red'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Customize title appearance\n",
    "p.title.text_color = 'blue'\n",
    "p.title.text_font_size = '18pt'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Customize legend\n",
    "p.legend.location = 'top_left'\n",
    "p.legend.label_text_font = 'times'\n",
    "p.legend.label_text_font_style = 'bold'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add circles as glyphs\n",
    "p.circle(x, y, size=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5, legend_label='Data Points')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display the plot\n",
    "show(p)\n"
   ]
