   "source": [
    "Q4. What is a Bokeh server, and how can you use it to create interactive plots that can be updated in\n",
    "real time?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "aa71ae8b-8c70-42a3-b1ca-3b64ad8b873a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A Bokeh server is a Python process that allows you to create and serve interactive Bokeh plots that can be updated in real time. With the Bokeh server, you can build web applications or dashboards that provide dynamic and interactive visualizations, allowing users to interact with the plots and see live updates.\n",
    "\n",
    "To use the Bokeh server and create interactive plots that can be updated in real time, you need to follow these steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "Import the necessary modules and functions from the Bokeh library:\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "from bokeh.plotting import figure, curdoc\n",
    "from bokeh.models import ColumnDataSource\n",
    "from bokeh.layouts import row\n",
    "from bokeh.io import show\n",
    "Prepare the data you want to plot. This can be done by creating lists or NumPy arrays for the initial data:\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "x = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "y = [6, 7, 2, 4, 5]\n",
    "Initialize the Bokeh figure object and create a ColumnDataSource to hold the data:\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "source = ColumnDataSource(data=dict(x=x, y=y))\n",
    "p = figure(title='My Bokeh Plot', x_axis_label='X-axis', y_axis_label='Y-axis')\n",
    "p.circle('x', 'y', source=source, size=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "Define a callback function that will be triggered when an event occurs, such as a button click or a slider value change. Inside the callback function, update the data in the ColumnDataSource:\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "def update_data():\n",
    "    # Update the data\n",
    "    new_x = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "    new_y = [9, 8, 7, 6, 5]\n",
    "    source.data = dict(x=new_x, y=new_y)\n",
    "Create the layout of the Bokeh plot by arranging the figure and any other interactive components (buttons, sliders, etc.):\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "# Create a button widget\n",
    "button = Button(label=\"Update Data\")\n",
    "button.on_click(update_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the layout\n",
    "layout = row(p, button)\n",
    "Create the Bokeh document (curdoc) and add the layout to it:\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "curdoc().add_root(layout)\n",
    "Run the Bokeh server:\n",
    "css\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "bokeh serve --show your_script.py\n",
    "Replace your_script.py with the name of your Python script.\n",
    "\n",
    "This will start the Bokeh server and open a browser window with the interactive plot. Any updates triggered by the event (in this case, the button click) will be reflected in the plot in real time.\n",
    "\n",
    "By using the Bokeh server, you can build dynamic and interactive visualizations that respond to user interactions or live data updates. The server facilitates the communication between the web browser and the Python process, allowing for real-time updates and interactivity."
   ]
  },
