   "source": [
    "Q5. How can you embed a Bokeh plot into a web page or dashboard using Flask or Django?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7226460a-49ad-44ea-9c17-9ab3587aa1ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To embed a Bokeh plot into a web page or dashboard using Flask or Django, you can follow these general steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "Install the necessary libraries:\n",
    "\n",
    "Flask: pip install flask\n",
    "Django: pip install django\n",
    "Create a Flask or Django project and set up the basic structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "Generate the Bokeh plot using the desired Bokeh functionality.\n",
    "\n",
    "For Flask:\n",
    "\n",
    "a. Import the necessary modules:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "from flask import Flask, render_template\n",
    "from bokeh.embed import components\n",
    "b. Create a Flask app:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "app = Flask(__name__)\n",
    "c. Define a Flask route to render the template with the embedded Bokeh plot:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "@app.route('/')\n",
    "def index():\n",
    "    # Generate the Bokeh plot\n",
    "    plot = generate_bokeh_plot()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extract the script and div components of the plot\n",
    "    script, div = components(plot)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Render the template with the embedded Bokeh plot\n",
    "    return render_template('index.html', script=script, div=div)\n",
    "d. Create the HTML template file (e.g., index.html) in the appropriate template folder (templates):\n",
    "\n",
    "html\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "<!DOCTYPE html>\n",
    "<html>\n",
    "<head>\n",
    "    <title>Embedded Bokeh Plot</title>\n",
    "    <!-- Include Bokeh's JavaScript and CSS files -->\n",
    "    {{ script|safe }}\n",
    "</head>\n",
    "<body>\n",
    "    <!-- Insert the Bokeh plot's div component -->\n",
    "    {{ div|safe }}\n",
    "</body>\n",
    "</html>\n",
    "e. Run the Flask app:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "    app.run(debug=True)\n",
    "For Django:\n",
    "\n",
    "a. Create a Django app:\n",
    "\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "python manage.py startapp myapp\n",
    "b. In the views.py file of your app, define a view to generate the Bokeh plot and render the template with the embedded plot:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "from django.shortcuts import render\n",
    "from bokeh.embed import components\n",
    "\n",
    "def index(request):\n",
    "    # Generate the Bokeh plot\n",
    "    plot = generate_bokeh_plot()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extract the script and div components of the plot\n",
    "    script, div = components(plot)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Render the template with the embedded Bokeh plot\n",
    "    return render(request, 'index.html', {'script': script, 'div': div})\n",
    "c. Create the HTML template file (e.g., index.html) in the appropriate template folder (myapp/templates/myapp):\n",
    "\n",
    "html\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "<!DOCTYPE html>\n",
    "<html>\n",
    "<head>\n",
    "    <title>Embedded Bokeh Plot</title>\n",
    "    <!-- Include Bokeh's JavaScript and CSS files -->\n",
    "    {{ script|safe }}\n",
    "</head>\n",
    "<body>\n",
    "    <!-- Insert the Bokeh plot's div component -->\n",
    "    {{ div|safe }}\n",
    "</body>\n",
    "</html>\n",
    "d. Define the URL pattern in urls.py to map to the view:\n",
    "\n",
    "python\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "from django.urls import path\n",
    "from myapp.views import index\n",
    "\n",
    "urlpatterns = [\n",
    "    path('', index, name='index'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "e. Run the Django server:\n",
    "\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "python manage.py runserver\n",
    "These steps provide a basic outline for embedding a Bokeh plot into a web page or dashboard using Flask or Django. You would need to adapt the code to your specific application and project structure."
   ]
